This paper deals with the issue of anonymity and privacy on the Internet, which is a common concern in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves data mining and information retrieval techniques to link user profiles based on their usernames, which falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the entropy of username strings, which is related to the field of cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper involves crawling real web services, which is a common technique in the field of web and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the possibility of linking user profiles based on usernames, which is related to the field of database systems (cs.DB).
